          "Robert Hooke",
          "1665",
          "Cellulae",
          "Cork"
        ],
        "teacherMoves": [
          "Show image of cork cells immediately to visualize the 'honeycomb' structure."
        ],
        "examples": [
          "A brick wall: bricks are like cells, mortar is intercellular material (though Hooke saw empty walls)."
