        "visuals": [
          "Diagram of Robert Hooke's microscope",
          "Image of cork under magnification"
        ]
      },
      {
        "conceptName": "Prokaryotic vs. Eukaryotic Cells",
        "definition": "Classification based on the presence or absence of a well-defined nucleus.",
        "coreExplanation": "Eukaryotes have a true nucleus and membrane-bound organelles (e.g., plants, animals). Prokaryotes lack a nuclear membrane and distinct organelles (e.g., bacteria, blue-green algae).",
