        "examples": [
          "Human cells = Eukaryotic",
          "E. coli bacteria = Prokaryotic"
        ],
        "visuals": [
          "Side-by-side comparison diagram of Bacteria vs. Animal Cell"
        ]
      },
      {
        "conceptName": "Cell Membrane and Wall",
        "definition": "Outer boundary regulating movement; rigid support structure in plants.",
        "coreExplanation": "The cell membrane is selectively permeable (allows some things, blocks others). The cell wall is non-living, made of cellulose in plants, providing shape and protection. Animal cells lack a cell wall.",
